1
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:47,959
MAN: "September 11, 1777.

2
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:49,799
"My loving wife,

3
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:54,391
"these past few months away from you
and Nathaniel have been difficult,

4
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:56,670
"and I miss both of you terribly.

5
00:00:58,480 --> 00:01:02,866
"We have all made sacrifices,
starting with our commander.

6
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:27,959
(GUN FIRING)

7
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:31,759
"We face the most
powerful army in the world.

8
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:35,225
"In our last battle we felt
the bite of their artillery."

9
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,546
Fire!

10
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:47,839
"But we held firm and
pushed them back.

11
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:51,199
"Our commander did not let us fail.

12
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:55,159
"We trust him. He keeps
our spirits high."

13
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:58,431
COMMANDER: Battalion, attention!

14
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:15,799
MAN:
"General Washington reminds us

15
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,839
"that life, liberty and
the pursuit of happiness

16
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:23,399
"are our unalienable rights and we
will not give them up to the crown.

17
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:26,559
"When the war is won,
America will be the first nation

18
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:29,079
"to freely choose its own way.

19
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:32,999
"Today will be another test of our
will as we face General Howe,

20
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,359
"whose troops outnumber
us by the thousands.

21
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:40,879
"The American cause now rests on
providence and General Washington."

22
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:44,679
Hold the line, boys!

23
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,679
Hold the line!

24
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:49,462
MAN: Ready, fire!

25
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:54,308
Fire!

26
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:59,101
Fire!

27
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:09,469
Charge!

28
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:16,824
(SHOUTING)

29
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:40,187
(WASHINGTON GRUNTING)

30
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,661
COMMANDER: General Washington!

31
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:47,159
Fall back! Retreat!

32
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:50,479
Fall back! Retreat!

33
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,479
- COMMANDER 1: Advance!
- COMMANDER 2: Retreat!

34
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:55,262
Fall back, company!

35
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:02,421
(GRUNTING)

36
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:37,071
DINESH D'SOUZA:
Imagine the unimaginable.

37
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:43,062
What if George Washington had
been killed by a sniper's bullet?

38
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:54,068
What if the Civil War had torn this
country into two or 10 countries?

39
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:02,862
What if Hitler got the
atomic bomb first?

40
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:13,947
What would the world look like
if America did not exist?

41
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,710
(RADIO CHATTERING)

42
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:09,703
MAN: (SINGING)
From farmers in the fields

43
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:15,542
to the tallest of the
towers that fall and rise

44
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:19,799
1-7-7-6, the names upon the list

45
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:24,630
of all the ones who
gave until they died

46
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:27,879
Don't you hold back

47
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,839
I can see in your mind

48
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:34,943
and your mind will set you free

49
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:40,919
Rise to the top of the world

50
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:43,199
America

51
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:48,110
America, don't you cry

52
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:51,239
Lift me up

53
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:54,199
Give me strength to press on

54
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:58,119
Rise to the top of the world

55
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,279
America

56
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:04,302
America, don't you cry

57
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:08,039
Lift me up

58
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:11,159
Give me strength to press on

59
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:13,479
Rise to the top of the world

60
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,670
D'SOUZA: I love America.

61
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,719
I chose this country.

62
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,879
(SINGING) America, don't you cry

63
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:24,879
D'SOUZA: And like millions of immigrants,
I've been blessed by my life in America.

64
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:28,559
(SINGING)
Give me strength to press on

65
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:31,239
D'SOUZA: This country does
something truly unique.

66
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:34,944
It allows you to write the
script of your own life.

67
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:45,679
A chapter of my script
was making the film 2016.

68
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:49,879
It surprised Hollywood and the
media by becoming a runaway hit.

69
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:54,266
It became the number two political
documentary film of all time.

70
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:58,919
In the film I made three predictions.

71
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:01,119
The federal government
would grow bigger

72
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:04,839
as America's role in the
world grows smaller.

73
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:09,199
Under President Obama,
the national debt would double.

74
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:12,319
This administration would
undermine our allies

75
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,909
and strengthen our enemies.

76
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:22,101
Seeing these predictions come true,
I'm scared for the future of America.

77
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:28,022
But I believe we can be strong again
unless we choose another path.

78
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:33,039
A century and a half ago,
a young Abraham Lincoln

79
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:35,902
issued a prophetic warning.

80
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:41,719
Shall we expect some
transatlantic military giant

81
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:44,879
to step the ocean and
crush us with a blow?

82
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:50,999
Never. All the armies of Europe,
Asia and Africa combined

83
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,279
with a Bonaparte for a commander

84
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:57,559
could not by force take
a drink from the Ohio.

85
00:10:57,560 --> 00:11:02,982
At what point then, is the
approach of danger to be expected?

86
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:08,799
I answer that if it ever reach us,
it must spring up from amongst us.

87
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:11,468
It cannot come from abroad.

88
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,399
If destruction be our lot,

89
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:19,119
then we ourselves must be
the author and finisher of it.

90
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:22,199
As a nation of freemen,

91
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:28,589
we must live throughout
all time or die by suicide.

92
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:34,239
D'SOUZA: How do you convince a great
nation to author its own destruction?

93
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:37,119
You start by telling a new story.

94
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,839
'Cause if you got a business,
you didn't build that.

95
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,919
(AUDIENCE AGREEING)

96
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:42,959
Somebody else made that happen.

97
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:45,119
D'SOUZA:
What President Obama is really saying

98
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,839
is that the wealth and
abundance of American life

99
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:51,350
are not earned, they're stolen.

100
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,959
But it's not just President Obama.

101
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:59,159
MICHAEL ERIC DYSON:
Thievery was a critical element

102
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:01,439
to the expansion of American empire.

103
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:04,159
MICHAEL MOORE:
This is a nation founded on genocide

104
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:08,865
- (AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)
- and built on the backs of slaves.

105
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:13,062
MAN: Moving borders.
They call it American imperialism.

106
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:15,119
D'SOUZA:
Obama didn't create this movement.

107
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,599
It created him.

108
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:21,199
JEREMIAH WRIGHT: Not God
bless America. God damn America.

109
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:25,639
WARD CHURCHILL: European expansion,
conquest, colonization, genocide.

110
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:28,759
HOWARD ZINN: American foreign
policy has been aggressive

111
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:31,319
and imperialist for a very long time.

112
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:36,519
It was expansionist immediately starting
right after the Revolutionary War.

113
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:38,519
D'SOUZA: Incredible as it may seem,

114
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:43,862
there are people in America who
want a world without America.

115
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:52,270
Their indictments against America
start at the very beginning.

116
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:11,061
(SHOUTING)

117
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,239
D'SOUZA:
What are the words that come to mind

118
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:16,989
when you hear the phrase,
Christopher Columbus?

119
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:19,666
(DOOR CLOSING)

120
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:29,670
I know your name.

121
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:32,260
What's your unit?

122
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:36,942
Lieutenant Colonel John Fer
of the United States Air Force.

123
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:43,559
And ends 400 years later in
America with the Trail of Tears

124
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:48,799
where 18,000 Native Americans
were forced to march 2,000 miles,

125
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:51,479
leaving a third of them dead.

126
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:55,423
What words come to mind when
you think of the word "America"?

127
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:59,319
A sadness. For me,
it's just a great sadness.

128
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:02,910
I think of all the hundreds of
nations that were destroyed.

129
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:25,919
D'SOUZA: In 1845, Mexican
territory covered most of Texas,

130
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:29,559
New Mexico, Arizona and California.

131
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,559
I like Chicano nationalism.

132
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:35,799
I really do prefer Hispanic
culture to Anglo-Saxon culture.

133
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:38,639
And you say, "Well, why don't
you move back to Mexico?"

134
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:41,119
I don't have to. I'm in Mexico.

135
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:43,199
And like I tell my Chicano students,

136
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:48,599
maybe after there isn't a United States,
we'll still be here, like the Indians.

137
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:51,479
D'SOUZA: So to put it biblically,
you are in America but not of America.

138
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:53,599
I'm not of America, no.

139
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:56,479
D'SOUZA: Charles Truxillo is a
professor of Chicano studies

140
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:59,439
at the University of New Mexico.

141
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:06,182
He's a leading representative of a movement
trying to reclaim Mexico's lost lands.

142
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:13,919
Did the United States steal half
of Mexico in the Mexican War?

143
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:20,479
Yes, and the wealth of those areas.
California, New Mexico, Arizona, Texas,

144
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:22,199
the oil, the minerals,

145
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:25,359
would have made Mexico
a premier economic power,

146
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:27,391
like it's becoming now.

147
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:31,839
When I went one time with my father
to Mexico to visit relatives,

148
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:33,879
we were in an old classroom

149
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:36,679
and they had a map of North
America up in the classroom.

150
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:39,759
And it had the area that's
the American Southwest

151
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:43,239
from Texas to California
cross-thatched

152
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:46,519
with the colors of Mexico
and the United States,

153
00:15:46,520 --> 00:15:52,226
and they had named that area
provincias perdidas, lost provinces.

154
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:09,559
They have killed us, beat us,

155
00:16:09,560 --> 00:16:12,559
drugged us, knocked us and
raped us and robbed us.

156
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:15,103
Done everything but the right thing.

157
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:19,319
MALCOLM X:
We don't see any American dream.

158
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:22,944
We've experienced only
the American nightmare.

159
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:29,239
WRIGHT: We took Africans from their
country to build our way of ease

160
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:33,501
and kept them enslaved
and living in fear.

161
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:39,679
DYSON: Well, obviously as
a black person in America,

162
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:44,039
it's, um, a part of the
wretched history of this nation

163
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:48,799
that my foremothers and forefathers
were not seen as fully human.

164
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:52,559
D'SOUZA: I spoke to the African
American scholar Michael Eric Dyson

165
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:54,719
at Georgetown University.

166
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:57,719
Has Obama's election
and re-election...

167
00:16:57,720 --> 00:17:00,599
Doesn't that say something
about the end of racism?

168
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:04,079
I would not deny at all that American
has made enormous progress.

169
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:05,759
Are we there yet? No.

170
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:08,759
America doesn't want to confront
the vicious inequalities

171
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:10,599
that it set loose in this nation.

172
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:14,439
Absorbing things that are not yours.
Taking stuff that is not yours.

173
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:19,079
We can say thievery was a critical element
to the expansion of American empire

174
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:22,750
and the establishment of
the American way of life.

175
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:26,639
D'SOUZA: 150 years ago
at the height of slavery,

176
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:31,879
another man made an even more
passionate indictment of America.

177
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:35,663
The American slave,
what is your 4th of July?

178
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:42,144
I answer a day that reveals to him
more than all other days in a year,

179
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:46,030
a gross injustice.

180
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:49,199
Your celebration is a sham.

181
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:54,479
You profess to believe that of
one blood God made all nations

182
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:58,919
and hath commanded all men
everywhere to love one another.

183
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:00,959
Yet, you notoriously hate

184
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:05,839
and glory in your hatred all men whose
skin are not colored like your own.

185
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:07,479
D'SOUZA: Meet Frederick Douglass.

186
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:10,159
Born a slave, he escaped to freedom

187
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:13,784
and became a champion of
the antislavery movement.

188
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:17,439
DOUGLASS: You can bare your bosom
to the storm of British artillery

189
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:19,559
to throw off a three-penny tax on tea

190
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:21,799
and yet wring the last
hard-earned farthing

191
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:25,390
from the grasp of the black
laborers of your country.

192
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:29,199
There is not a nation on the earth

193
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:32,679
guilty of practices more shocking

194
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:34,719
and bloody

195
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:40,062
than are the people of the United
States, than on this 4th of July.

196
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:54,319
BILL AYERS: We like to think of
ourselves as a peace-loving people.

197
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:57,679
If they said, "We're going in for the
oil," we'd say, "No, don't do it."

198
00:18:57,680 --> 00:19:00,382
But instead they say,
"We're going in for democracy."

199
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:05,919
Has the United States been a force
for good or ill in the world?

200
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:08,719
For the people we conquer,

201
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:12,390
the Vietnamese, we killed
a couple million of them,

202
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:15,427
not a force for good.

203
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:29,119
D'SOUZA: MIT professor Noam Chomsky
is a leading critic of American imperialism.

204
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:33,439
There's a reason why most of the
world regards the United States

205
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:36,159
as a predatory colonial power.

206
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:40,079
We overthrew the democratic
government of Guatemala in 1954,

207
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:44,399
Iran in 1953, Cuba in 1961.

208
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:49,310
Then Brazil, Chile,
Uruguay, Argentina,

209
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:52,667
on through the world.
It's not a pretty record.

210
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,831
(SHOUTING)

211
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:05,479
We are the 99%!

212
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:08,719
Whose street? Our street!
Occupy Wall Street!

213
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,759
We've never had anything
like this in this country

214
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:13,239
where we take on
economic issues like this.

215
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:16,719
If you want money, after you get
that million, you want a billion.

216
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:20,479
After you get a billion, you want a trillion.
After you get a trillion, you want a zillion.

217
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:23,262
There is no end. There is no line.

218
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:27,639
D'SOUZA: The charge against capitalism
is that greedy, selfish business owners

219
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:30,024
steal from people.

220
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:35,879
They create gross inequality by
depriving people of their fair share.

221
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:38,999
OBAMA: And it's only right that we ask
everyone to pay their fair share.

222
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,959
Asking everyone to
pay their fair share.

223
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:42,159
Pay their fair share.

224
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:46,559
There is nobody in this country
who got rich on his own.

225
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:47,759
Nobody.

226
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:50,399
You built a factory out there.
Good for you.

227
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:53,679
But I want to be clear,
you moved your goods

228
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:56,879
to market on the roads
the rest of us paid for.

229
00:20:56,880 --> 00:21:01,599
You hired workers the rest
of us paid to educate.

230
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:05,279
You were safe in your factory

231
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:11,146
because of police forces and fire
forces that the rest of us paid for.

232
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,719
D'SOUZA: It doesn't matter
whether you're making profits

233
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:18,559
from a hot dog stand in Times Square

234
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:22,662
or if you're the biggest
company on NASDAQ,

235
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:26,586
capitalists are under fire.

236
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:31,959
MOORE: Until we change the system,
and let's use the C word here.

237
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:34,039
We're talking about capitalism.

238
00:21:34,040 --> 00:21:37,279
If it's a more comfortable
word for you, greed.

239
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:39,559
That's just another word for it.

240
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:41,799
This ultimately has to change.

241
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,959
How much more are you
going to make them suffer?

242
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:49,551
Because some day they're
not gonna take it anymore.

243
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:56,239
D'SOUZA: These are the
indictments against America.

244
00:21:56,240 --> 00:22:00,039
We stole the country from
the Native Americans.

245
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:03,799
We took half of Mexico
in the Mexican War.

246
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:07,359
We stole the labor of
the African Americans.

247
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:13,464
And today our foreign policy and our
free market system are forms of theft.

248
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:21,599
These indictments developed separately
and each has been around for a long time.

249
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:27,119
But now they've come together in a
single narrative of American shame.

250
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:29,879
One professor pulled
this narrative together.

251
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:32,519
His name is Howard Zinn.

252
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:36,599
ZINN: I prefer to try to tell the
story of the discovery of America

253
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:38,679
from the viewpoint of the Arawaks.

254
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:41,959
Of the Constitution from the
standpoint of the slaves.

255
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:46,221
Of Andrew Jackson as
seen by the Cherokees.

256
00:22:49,120 --> 00:22:51,439
D'SOUZA: Matt Damon and Ben
Affleck grew up in the same

257
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:53,919
South Boston neighborhood as Zinn.

258
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:57,919
They gave him a nice plug in
their movie Good Will Hunting.

259
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,679
You want to read a real history book,

260
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,759
read Howard Zion's People's
History of the United States.

261
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:03,639
That book will knock you on your ass.

262
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:07,519
D'SOUZA: Zion's book has made
him quite the celebrity.

263
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:10,079
What I didn't realize is that
from the very beginning,

264
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:13,159
from when Columbus met the Arawaks,

265
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:18,184
there was... It was just nonstop, um,

266
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:23,519
violence and, uh, (EXHALING)
and, uh, just taking over.

267
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:26,479
They're bullying people and
taking over their resources.

268
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:30,479
D'SOUZA: Howard Zinn is the most influential
historian of the past 50 years.

269
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:32,839
His book has sold over
two million copies,

270
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:36,799
becoming required reading in most
colleges and many high schools.

271
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,319
Even Tony Soprano's
kid had to read it.

272
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:41,839
His history teacher, Mr. Cushman,

273
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:44,119
is teaching your son that if
Columbus was alive today,

274
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:46,679
he would go on trial for
crimes against humanity,

275
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:49,621
like Milošević in, you know, Europe.

276
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,599
Your teacher said that?

277
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:54,199
It's not just my teacher.
It's the truth.

278
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:56,345
It's in my history book.

279
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:59,501
(GUN FIRING)

280
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:12,787
D'SOUZA: This is the new
story of American shame.

281
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:20,199
Are our lives,
innocent on the surface,

282
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:25,986
part of a ruthless engine of
looting, exploitation and murder?

283
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:28,559
It's a powerful critique.

284
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:33,709
We can't just dismiss it with chants
of liberty, freedom, rah, rah, rah.

285
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:37,759
The critics are raising the
primary question of justice.

286
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:42,510
ALL:
...with liberty and justice for all.

287
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:46,639
D'SOUZA:
Read the Declaration of independence.

288
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:49,786
It's a cry against injustice.

289
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:56,790
For the American founders, liberty
was the solution to that injustice.

290
00:24:58,240 --> 00:25:01,839
This is not just an attack on the 1%.

291
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:05,119
It's an attack on all of us.

292
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:08,239
We are a nation of
immigrants and settlers.

293
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:12,547
And we are the ones
accused of these crimes.

294
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:19,429
If these things are true,
something has to be done about them.

295
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:30,665
(DOORBELL RINGING)

296
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:32,679
- There he is.
- How's it going?

297
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:35,239
- Good. Come on in.
- Good to see you.

298
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:37,839
- Been a while, hasn't it?
